  "title": "Harden realtime interaction jank during tool call",
  "description": "v2 (post-expert-review): Bind appServerEventDeliverHub to per-event createEventBackpressure via createEventHub.publish(payload), status-only coalesceKey, and snapshot-only dropPolicy; keep BatchedTauriEventSink strictly lossless with critical bypass; add Rust SnapshotThrottle (32ms per (workspaceId, itemId, kind)) for item/updated text snapshots; introduce useRenderScheduler hook (T-2 reuse) for requestIdleCallback + 8ms budget + input pending yield; add useToolOutputTailGate for stdout/stderr storms (append-buffer throttle + 60s sliding window; no generic last-write coalesce); collapse onAgentMessageCompleted's 5 dispatches into flushAgentCompletedBatch; split handleItemUpdate dispatch into urgent/transition/idle via renderSchedulingPolicy (N-1 rename); accumulate background items over 3 frames with active-thread-switch clear; expose streamingScheduleTier flag (baseline/guarded/aggressive) with full rollback. Add task 0.1/0.2 baseline-and-preflight (V-1) to fill in placeholder metrics before archive gate 11.1. OpenSpec change: openspec/changes/2026-06-24-harden-realtime-interaction-jank-during-tool-call/",
